1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Na3 {[%cal Ba3c4][%csl Rc4] In order to take the pawn 
back!} e5 $6 {Black wants to weaken White's Queen-side structure with ...Bxa3.} 
({Apart from} 3... g6) ({and} 3... e5 {,}) ({the main course also considers} 
3... c5 {,}) (3... a6) ({and} 3... Nf6 {.}) 4. Nxe5 {Sacrificing a pawn thinking 
that, ...Bxa3 followed by ...Qd4 will be strong but,} Bxa3 5. Qa4+ $5 {[%cal 
Ba4a3][%csl Ra3,Re8]} Bd7 6. Nxd7 Qxd7 7. Qxa3 $16 {[%csl Gc1,Gf1,Rc4] White is 
better thanks to the Bishop pair advantage, and is almost a pawn up! The c4-pawn 
is also very weak.} *

