1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 d4 3. b4 $1 {Reversed Benko.} g6 4. g3 {[%cal Bf1g2,Gg2a8][%csl 
Ge4,Gd5] With Black's d-pawn being pushed to d4, it means the f1-Bishop will be 
perfectly placed along the h1-a8 diagonal.} Bg7 {[%cal Gg7a1,Bd4d3][%csl Ra1] 
Threatening d3 to attack the a1-Rook!} 5. d3 {[%csl Gd3,Rd4]} e5 6. Bg2 Ne7 7. 
O-O O-O 8. a4 $5 {[%cal Ba4a5,Bb4b5] Taking more space on the Queenside and 
preparing for Ra2-Re2 idea later on.} a5 9. b5 {[%csl Gb5,Ga4,Gc4]} c5 10. Ra2 
{[%cal Be2e3,Gg7a1,Be3d4,Ba2e2][%csl Ra1]} Ra7 {Moving the Rook away from the 
g2-Bishop's eye.} 11. e3 {after the Queenside got closed, White has to attack 
the center!} dxe3 {otherwise White will be taking and doubling up the Rooks on 
the e-file!} 12. fxe3 b6 {opening the 7th rank for the a7-Rook to participate in 
the game.} 13. Nc3 {[%csl Gd5,Ge4]} Rd7 {[%cal Gd8d3][%csl Gd8,Gd7,Rd3]} 14. Ne1 
{[%cal Ge1d3]} f5 15. e4 $5 {[%cal Be4f5,Ba2e2][%csl Re5,Rf5] White wants to 
take exf5 in order to open the e-file against the e5-pawn.} f4 16. Raf2 $14 
{[%cal Bg3f4,Bc1b2,Gb2g7,Bc3d5][%csl Rf4,Re5,Gd5] Plan: Nd5-gxf4 and (at the 
proper time) Bb2 to add pressure on the e5-pawn.} *

