1. Nf3 c5 2. c4 Nc6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. Nc3 e6 {This move creates weaknesses 
around the Black King, so it is a good move trying to open up the game!} 6. d4 
$1 cxd4 7. Nb5 {Threatening Nd6+ in order to take Black's castling rights away! 
Another idea is to take the pawn back.} d6 8. Nfxd4 Nxd4 9. Nxd4 {[%csl Rd6] Now 
Black has a weak pawn on d6.} Ne7 10. O-O O-O 11. Bg5 $1 {[%cal 
Gd6d5,Gg5e7][%csl Re7] The point is to get rid of Knight which would otherwise 
support the d5-push.} h6 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Qd2 $14 {[%cal 
Bd4b5,Bf1d1,Gd1d6,Gb5d6][%csl Rd6,Gd2,Gd1] This leaves Black with the weak 
d6-pawn! Plan: Rfd1-Nb5!} *

