1. Nf3 Nc6 {The Chigorin Defence.} 2. d4 {[%cal Bd4d5][%csl Rc6] *General 
Plans:* Black improves the Queen's Knight first and one of the ideas is to 
castle long. White will be waiting to see where Black's King will go, if it goes 
to the Queenside the attack will be starting there, if it goes to the Kingside 
then the attack will be in the center. *Ideas:* • If Black castles long the 
attack will be starting with c3 followed by b4, building a pawn storm on the 
Queenside. • If Black castles short the attack will be mainly aimed at the 
d5-square by pushing the c4-pawn followed by Ne5 to open up the diagonal for the 
light-squared Bishop.} d5 3. g3 $5 {[%cal Bf1g2,Be1g1] Avoiding the early c4 
will avoid any possible counterplay on the d4-pawn!} Bf5 {Morozevich's usual 
choice in this position.} ({The main course also considers} 3... Bg4 {- 16 
variations.}) 4. Bg2 Qd7 5. O-O O-O-O ({The main course also considers Black 
delaying queenside castling (or forgoing it altogether) with} 5... e6 {- 24 
variations.}) 6. c4 dxc4 7. Qa4 {[%cal Bf3e5,Gg2b7,Ga4a7][%csl Rb7,Rc6,Ra7] Here 
White gets very dangerous attacking chances, for example:} e6 8. Ne5 $1 Nxe5 9. 
Qxa7 $1 {[%cal Ba7a8,Ba7b7,Gg2b7][%csl Rb7,Rc8]} c6 10. dxe5 Qd4 11. Qxd4 Rxd4 
12. Be3 {[%csl Rd4]} Rd5 $5 {Black is trying to sacrifice the exchange so that 
he can repair his pawn structure.} 13. Bxd5 exd5 14. b3 {[%cal 
Bc4b3,Ba2b3,Ga1a8] Whenever you are up an exchange try to open more files for 
your rooks.} Bb4 15. Rc1 {[%cal Gb3c4,Gc1c4][%csl Rc4]} Ne7 16. bxc4 Rd8 17. Bb6 
$16 {[%cal Ba2a6][%csl Gc1,Ga1] White is simply an exchange up. Plan: a4-a5-a6 
in order to open more files for the rooks.} *

